The paper discusses the development of hardware and software systems for Micro Aerial Vehicles (MAVs) with autonomous capabilities, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also extensively discusses computer vision (cs.CV) and probabilistic robotics (cs.AI) methods used in the system. The use of optimal control (cs.SY) and the high success rate of visual servoing (cs.LG) also suggest these categories as likely sub-categories.
